The '''University of Sanbra''', on [[Sanbra]], was renowned for its [[sentientologist]] and [[xenobiology]] programs. ''[[The University of Sanbra Guide to Intelligent Life]]'' was written by [[Tem Eliss]] from his experiences in these programs.

During the [[Republic Dark Age]], the [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lord]] [[Odion]] [[Raid on Sanbra|sacked]] the University of Sanbra at the behest of his uncle [[Chagras]], and he seized some research that had been compiled by the university on the [[Helm of Ieldis]], a legendary [[Sith artifact/Legends|Sith artifact]].<ref name="KE 14">[[Knight Errant: Escape 4|''Knight Errant: Escape'' 4]]</ref>

[[Pirate/Legends|Pirate]] [[Callow Batta]] had been a professor of governmental and [[Politics/Legends|political]] history college at Sanbra for almost 20 years.<ref name="AIR">''[[Alliance Intelligence Reports]]''</ref> [[Eppington]] was another professor on the faculty.<ref name="The University of Sanbra Guide to Intelligent Life: The Nosaurians">{{GamerCite|9|The University of Sanbra Guide to Intelligent Life: The Nosaurians}}.</ref> [[Professor/Legends|Profex]] [[Rynalla]], a [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]] scholar and secret adept, was affiliated with the department of ancient history of the University of Sanbra. She researched the lost ways of the Sith in the campus and discovered that a lost Sith treasure known as the [[Bracers of Najus]] was in the remains of a crashed starship in the planet [[Leritor/Legends|Leritor]], which prompted her to go to the world and recover it. Another related trail in the University archives connected the wrecked Sith ship with an equally forgotten and trap-laden Sith fortress.<ref name="g10">{{GamerCite|10|Standoff on Leritor}}</ref> [[Mankuskett]] was the Chair of Metagrowth and Polymorphism of the university who traveled to [[Endor/Legends|Endor]] in order to study its various lifeforms. [[Henrietya Antilles|Corellia Antilles]] was employed by the University of Sanbra as a xenoarchaeologist.<ref name="The Essential Atlas">''[[The Essential Atlas]]''</ref>

The University had a branch research campus on the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] starship ''[[Chu'unthor]]''.<ref name="Jedi Academy Training Manual">''[[Jedi Academy Training Manual]]''</ref> The [[Q'Maere Research Facility]] was originally a scientific outpost established by University of Sanbra to study exotic branches of planetology and [[xenobiology]] within the [[Kathol Rift/Legends|Kathol Rift]].<ref name="Harm's Way">''{{DarkStryder|adventure=Harm's Way|book=The Kathol Rift}}''</ref>

